OSINT Challenge Write-Ups
December 1st, 2024 – Legendary Watch
When I first looked at the image, I immediately noticed part of a watch dial. The visible text showed “SEIKO” and “CHRONOGRAPH AUTOMATIC.” 
The dial also had a distinctive orange/gold color with a Pepsi-style bezel (red and blue) and a day/date window displaying “SUN 18.”

Step 1 – Identify the Watch

My first step was to search for the visible text and visual features. I used queries like:
Seiko orange dial chronograph automatic
Seiko chronograph orange dial Pepsi bezel
Very quickly, the results pointed toward the famous Seiko “Pogue.”
This watch is well known among collectors because it was worn by astronaut William Pogue during a NASA mission.

Step 2 – Research Why It Is “Legendary”
To confirm the significance of the watch, I searched:
Seiko Pogue's history
Why is the Seiko Pogue famous
I discovered that the watch became legendary because Colonel William Pogue wore it during the Skylab 4 mission, 
making it one of the first automatic chronographs worn in space.

Step 3 – Find the Launch Date
The challenge question asked:
On what date did it take off?
Since the watch went to space during Skylab 4, I searched:
Skylab 4 launch date
This revealed that the mission launched on November 16, 1973.

Step 4 – Convert to Required Format
The challenge required the answer in YYYYMMDD format.
So I converted:
November 16, 1973 → 19731116
Final Answer

19731116
